.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
Returns \fIflag\fP = true if the communication associated with the status
object was canceled successfully. In such a case, all other fields of
status (such as \fIcount\fP or \fItag\fP) are undefined. Otherwise, returns
\fIflag\fP = false. If a receive operation might be canceled, one should
call \fI\%MPI_Test_cancelled\fP first, to check whether the operation was
canceled, before checking on the other fields of the return status.
.SH NOTES
.sp
Cancel can be an expensive operation that should be used only
exceptionally.
